{"id": "duc04-testb-49:7#21", "contents": "World leaders, including President Clinton and British Prime Minister Tony Blair, have finally begun to address the issue of wildfires, after months of silence. Their fear, as expressed by their advisers, is that 15 months of financial turmoil are now threatening political stability. This concern has turned the current meeting into a complex mix of worries and a search for both short-term and long-term solutions. Different countries, such as Japan, France, and Southeast Asia, have arrived in Washington with varying diagnoses of the problem and proposed solutions."}
